	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wizards can do more dd than any other class(with about 1600 damage with their highest spell), they have the root ability, they are the masters of teleporting, and their stun become some of the most important spells they have. I have a few tactics that all wizards need to develop.  First off is the ever famous root and nuke. To perform this effectively you will need to practice root to keep it from fizzling as much.  In order to perform this you root the enemy and if they dont resist fire some of your powerful evocation spells however you will need to save some mana in case you cant get the creature down enough to finish him off the extra man will be used for evacuation spells. The best move is to put money into great int boosters therefore highering your mana.  Another tactic that can be used is the root, nuke, and fade.  For the person who said that fade is worthless wake up this spell can be used very effectively if you practice it.  This tactic starts the same way as the regular root and nuke technique but when the mob comes at you with good hp left use the fade technique to gain position on the mob. If you do this properly all you have to do is root and nuke again. Another tactic that I haven't used as much is the levitate. When attacking a creature that does not cast magic or carry a throwing/projectile weapon (such as Ambassador D'vinn) and you can get into an area without a low ceiling then this technique will render the mob attckless just levitate and blast it until it is dead. These are great tactics for a solo mid to low level wiz.  As you get more advanced you will want to develop your stun spells a little more for these spells, if they stick, give the wizard complete control over the situation. I hope this helps you wizzies who love to solo.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
