	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello everyone. I'm a lvl 31 Wiz on the Morell Thule server. Many people think that wizards are a worthless class because all the do it DD. Why have a wizard when you can get a druid who nukes, heals, buffs and ports. Because druid nukes SUCK. Druids can nuke your neighbor's dog off your lawn but that's about it. Second,  wizards _can_ nuke. All you need is Jboots or lots of cash to buy sow potions or a lv 30+ ranger ;). On lvl 29 wizards get an Area of Effect Snare spell - bonds of force. Whenever i can, i kite. I think that wizards are a strong solo class, no match for necros but hey, and that we can solo yellows and lower mobs easily. As long as you only pull one at a time. Also, I played my wiz a long time because I'm young and stupid but, i have some info for all of you grouping wizzies.<br><br>Lvls 1-10 applies to wizards starting on Faydwer.<br><br>Lv 1-4 do the mail quest in Felwithe-Kelethin. Good xp, faction and cash.<br>Lv 5-8 test you mettle on Orc Hill near Kelethin.<br>Lv 8-12  can be spent in Crushbone (my fav zone)<br>Lv 12-14 Dervish Cutthroats in North Ro.<br>Lv 14-17 Oasis - Crocs=xp Orcs=lewt<br>Lv 18-20 Gnolls Gnolls Gnolls (Highkeep Pass - Gnoll ledge)<br>Lv 20-25 Highkeep Hold - Guard room<br>Lv 25-30 Highkeep Hold - warrior/raider Rooms<br>Lv 27-30 (Solo) - Brutes in Warslicks Woods on Kunark<br>Lv 30-35 - Dalnir. Second Floor or Ent.<br><br>So far I haven't gotten past that but I'll keep trying. <br>Good luck fellow nukers!<br><br> - Ianarie Everbright<br>Master Nuker and Master Drinker<br>Major Druid flamer<br>Always happy to help, just drop me a line on Morell-Thule =)   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
